keyValuePair.Value: How pleased are you to get through the Group Stage?
So, you've secured qualification from the Group Stage. That's an achievement in itself. What happens now? How far can this team go?
This is only the beginning, I hope.

I want us to be ambitious. I want these players to believe they can achieve great things. If we can continue being strong at the back and cool in front of goal, then maybe this is only the start of the adventure!
We've got a good spirit.

This team has a great spirit. We fight tooth and nail for everything, stand up strong in every challenge. If we add a little more creativity and be a bit more ruthless in front of goal, we can go on to achieve great things, I believe.
Qualifying was a minimum requirement.
We've qualified and, of course, I congratulate the players on that. But we have to be focused now. We've achieved nothing yet. Getting through the Group Stage is only the start for this team.
Can you make it out of the group?
It's a very competitive group. Looking at the games still to come, do you think %1s are in a good position to make the knock-out stages of the competition?
It's time to be positive.

In one or two games, we've had to work very hard defensively to keep ourselves in contention. Now we need one or two positive results to see us reach the knock-outs. I want the lads to take control of their own destinies now and get us out of the group.
I'm happy with our situation.

As you probably know, this competition isn't our main priority this year. So I'm pleased we're still in contention and, obviously, qualifying for the knock-out stages would be a real boost for the whole squad.
We should already be through!

I've haven't seen us hit top gear with our attacking play in this group so far. It's only our spirit and our defensive organisation that's really kept us in contention. I look at the players we have available and, to be honest, I think we should already have qualified. Now's the time for everybody to stand up strong so we can get the job done.
Pleased to go through as %1s group winners?
You already knew you were through but now %1s have been confirmed as group winners. Is that a big advantage, knowing you'll avoid the top seeds in the first knock-out round?
Let's take nothing for granted.

Of course winning the group should give us a better chance to progress. But you can't take anything for granted in the %1s. We'll need to be well-organised defensively and ruthless up top against whoever we draw in the first knock-out round.

Of course winning the group should give us a better chance to progress. But you can't take anything for granted in the %1s. We'll need to be well-organised defensively and ruthless up top against whoever we draw in the first knock-out round.
Our attacking play has been the difference.

Our attacking play is what's set us apart in all our group games. I'm very pleased we'll avoid the top seeds in the next round, of course, but we know we'll need to improve defensively whoever we face in the %1s from now on.
We've achieved nothing yet.
Of course we're happy to be through and happy to have won the group. But this is only the start of the journey. We're not going to go crazy. We know we haven't achieved anything yet.
What went wrong for your boys?
So %1s are out at the group stage of the %2s. What are your thoughts? What let your boys down?
We just came up short.

Football's simple, right? We didn't score enough goals and we let too many in. That's the end of us in the %1s for this season. But we'll keep our heads up. We gave it our best shot in every single game. We'll be better next time round.
Maybe we took our eye off the ball.

We looked at the %1s this season and, right from the start, we knew it wasn't going to be our main priority. It's been a good experience but, now we're out, we won't dwell on the disappointment. We've got plenty still to play for this season.
We've just not been good enough.

We really hoped to reach the knock-out rounds this season. But I hope the younger players, especially, will have learnt a lot from this experience. In the %1s, every mistake gets punished. We competed in every game, of course. But, in the end, we just weren't good enough to go through.
